wrk
------------------------------------------
wrk is a modern HTTP benchmarking tool capable of generating significant load
when run on a single multi-core CPU. It combines a multithreaded design with
scalable event notification systems such as epoll and kqueue.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.3.5-1
  libssl1.1-1.1.1o-1
  luajit-2.0.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.38-1
  cygport-0.35.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  libssl-devel-1.1.1o-1
  luajit-devel-2.0.4-1
  make-4.3-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/wg/wrk/

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/wg/wrk/archive/refs/tags/4.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack wrk-4.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./wrk-4.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/wrk-4.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/wrk-4.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(wrk)
  /usr/bin/wrk.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/wrk.README
  /usr/share/doc/wrk/CHANGES
  /usr/share/doc/wrk/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/wrk/NOTICE
  /usr/share/doc/wrk/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/wrk/SCRIPTING

